/                   → Root (top of everything)
├── bin/            → Essential commands (ls, cp, mv)
├── sbin/           → System admin commands (fdisk, ifconfig)
├── etc/            → Configuration files
├── home/           → User home directories
│   └── abc/      → Your personal folder
├── root/           → Root user's home
├── var/            → Variable data (logs, databases)
│   └── log/        → System logs
├── tmp/            → Temporary files (deleted on reboot)
├── usr/            → User programs
│   ├── bin/        → Non-essential commands
│   └── lib/        → Libraries
├── lib/            → Shared system libraries
├── dev/            → Device files (sda, tty, null)
├── proc/           → Process info (virtual filesystem)
├── sys/            → System/hardware info (virtual)
├── mnt/            → Mount points for external drives
├── media/          → Auto-mounted drives (USB, CD)
├── opt/            → Optional/third-party software
└── boot/           → Boot files, kernel
